    "helpContent": {
      "html": "<div class='help-container'><h1>LingoPro User Guide</h1><h2>1. Getting Started</h2><p>LingoPro is a text analysis tool for linguistic research and NLP tasks.</p><h3>1.1 Loading Content</h3><ul><li><b>URL Input</b>: Enter Wikipedia URLs in the address bar</li><li><b>Local Files</b>: Select .txt files using the file browser button</li><li>Click <b>GET</b> to load content</li></ul><h3>1.2 Navigation Tabs</h3><ul><li><b>Original</b>: Raw text with sentence numbering</li><li><b>Processed</b>: Search results with highlighting</li><li><b>Statistic Info</b>: Text metrics and POS distribution</li></ul><h2>2. Search Features</h2><h3>2.1 Search Parameters</h3><ul><li><b>Exact Word</b>: Search for specific word forms</li><li><b>Word's Lemma</b>: Search by base word form</li><li><b>POS Tag</b>: Search by part-of-speech (e.g., NOUN, VERB)</li><li><b>Regex</b>: Advanced pattern matching</li><li><b>Neighbors</b>: Context words around matches</li><li><b>Case Sensitive</b>: Toggle case sensitivity</li></ul><h3>2.2 Key Search Logic</h3><ul><li><b>AND Relationship</b>: When multiple conditions are set (exact word, lemma, POS tag), results must match ALL conditions</li><li><b>Highlight Colors</b>:<ul><li>Exact matches: <span style='background-color:#FFEB3B; color:black; padding:0 3px;'>Yellow highlight</span></li><li>Left neighbors: <span style='background-color:#2196F3; color:white; padding:0 3px;'>Blue highlight</span></li><li>Right neighbors: <span style='background-color:#4CAF50; color:white; padding:0 3px;'>Green highlight</span></li></ul></li></ul><h3>2.3 Executing Searches</h3><ol><li>Set your search parameters</li><li>Click <b>Search</b> to view results in Processed tab</li><li>Use <b>Clear</b> to reset all fields</li></ol><h2>3. Managing Results</h2><h3>3.1 Search History</h3><ul><li>Each search is automatically added to History panel</li><li>Displays time, document name, search conditions, and match count</li><li>Newest searches appear at the top</li></ul><h3>3.2 Saving Results</h3><ol><li>Click <b>Save Search History</b> in History panel</li><li>Select destination folder</li><li>All searches from current session are saved as XML file</li><li>File contains complete search details and results</li></ol><h2>4. Statistical Analysis</h2><ul><li><b>Text Statistics</b>: Word counts, sentence counts, average word length</li><li><b>Top Frequent Words</b>: Automatically filters out common stop words</li><li><b>POS Distribution</b>: Visual percentage breakdown of parts-of-speech</li><li>Updated automatically when new content is loaded</li></ul></div>",
